  </objectDesc>\n                        <handDesc>\n                            <handNote><p>Irregular letters, cursive A, Μ and Ω, lunate Ε and Σ.</p><!--measurements from Korhonen-->\n                                <locus from=\"line1\" to=\"line3\">Lines 1-3</locus>\n                                <dimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    <height unit=\"mm\">8-15</height>\n                                </dimensions>\n                                <locus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2</locus>\n                                <dimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    <height unit=\"mm\">not recorded</height>\n                                </dimensions>\n                            </handNote>\n                        </handDesc>\n                    </physDesc>\n                    <history>\n                        <origin>\n                            <origPlace>\n                                <placeName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462270\">Catina</placeName>\t\t\n                                <placeName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2525068\">Catania</placeName>\n                            \t<geo>37.49223, 15.07041</geo>\n\t\t</origPlace>\n                            <origDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"0301\" notAfter-custom=\"0500\" precision=\"low\">4th — 5th century CE</origDate>\n                        </origin>\n                        <provenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\" when=\"1740\">Found in 1740 \"in Stesichori area\", Catania (Amico).</provenance>\n                        <provenance type=\"observed\">Observed by Amico in Museo Biscari, later by Korhonen in Magazzino del cortile, Collezione Biscari (formerly sala VI 89).</provenance>\n                        <provenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\">None</provenance>\n                        <acquisition/>\n                    </history>\n                </msDesc>\n            </sourceDesc>\n        </fileDesc>\n        <encodingDesc>\n             <p>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines</p>\n             <xi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 <xi:fallback>\n                     <p>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values</p>\n                 </xi:fallback>\n             </xi:include>\n\t  <xi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     <xi:fallback>\n\t       <p>ISicily glyphs authority list</p>\n\t     </xi:fallback>\n\t   </xi:include>\n         </encodingDesc>\n        <profileDesc>\n            <calendarDesc>\n                <calendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    <p>Julian Calendar</p>\n                </calendar>\n            </calendarDesc>\n            <langUsage>\n                <language ident=\"en\">English</language>\n                <language ident=\"it\">Italian</language>\n                <language ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek</language>\n                <language ident=\"la\">Latin</language>\n                <language ident=\"he\">Hebrew</language>\n                <language ident=\"phn\">Phoenician</language>\n                <language ident=\"xpu\">Punic</language>\n                <language ident=\"osc\">Oscan</language>\n                <language ident=\"xly\">Elymian</language>\n                <language ident=\"scx\">Sikel</language>\n                <language ident=\"sxc\">Sikan</language>\n            </langUsage>\n            <textClass>\n                <keywords scheme=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins.html\">\n                    <term ana=\"#function.funerary\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html\">funerary</term>\n                </keywords>\n            </textClass>\n        </profileDesc>\n        <revisionDesc status=\"draft\">\n            <listChange>\n                <change when=\"2016-12-03\" who=\"#JCu\">James Cummings autogenerated EpiDoc output from database</change>\n                <change when=\"2019-09-02\" who=\"#AA\">Alex Antoniou Epidoc editing and English translation</change>\n            \t   <change when=\"2020-10-05\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova normalised Unicode</change>\n            \t   <change when=\"2020-10-08\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova updated list of languages</change>\n\t\t<change when=\"2020-11-26\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova restructured bibliography</change>\n\t    <change when=\"2020-12-18\" who=\"#system\">Updated Zenodo DOI</change>\n            \t<change when=\"2021-01-19\" who=\"#SS\">renumbered files, uris and references</change>\n                <change when=\"2022-12-22\" who=\"#martaf\">Marta Fogagnolo revised the text encoding, added dimensions, translations and commentary</change>\n\t</listChange>\n        </revisionDesc>\n    </teiHeader>\n    <facsimile>\n        <surface type=\"front\">\n            <graphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic003287_tiled.tif\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                <desc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana</desc>\n            </graphic>\n            <graphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic003287.jpg\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                <desc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana</desc>\n            </graphic>\n         </surface>\n    </facsimile>\n    <text>\n        <body>\n            <div type=\"edition\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"grc\" resp=\"#martaf #AA\">\n                <ab>\n                    <lb n=\"0\"/><gap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"line\"/><lb n=\"1\" break=\"no\"/><w part=\"F\">σειν</w> <orig>Μ<unclear>ΛΖ</unclear></orig><gap reason=\"illegible\" quantity=\"1\" unit=\"character\"/> <w>παρακι<lb n=\"2\" break=\"no\"/>μένην</w> <w>τῷ</w> <w>ναῷ</w> <persName><name><choice><orig>Ἱλάρω<lb n=\"3\" break=\"no\"/>νος</orig><reg>Ἱλαρίωνος</reg></choice></name></persName>\n                </ab>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"apparatus\" resp=\"#martaf\">\n                <listApp>\n                    <app><note>Text based on photograph</note></app>\n                    <app loc=\"line 1\"><note>Korhonen: -σειν could be the end of an infinitive</note></app>\n                    <app loc=\"line 1\"><note>After M are traces of three letters, the first probably a Λ or Α (Λ for Amico, H for Ferrara, Μ for Korhonen), the second a Ζ and the third perhaps a punctuation mark</note></app>\n                    <app loc=\"lines 2-3\"><note>Amico, Ferrara, lapis: ΙΛΑΡΩ|ΝΟΣ; Korhonen: Ἱλαρ<supplied reason=\"omitted\">ί</supplied>ω|νος</note></app>\n                </listApp>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#martaf\">\n                <p>… laid down in the church of Hilarion.</p>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"it\" resp=\"#martaf\">\n                <p>… deposta nella chiesa di Ilarione.</p>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"commentary\" resp=\"#martaf\">\n                <p>The epitaph form has no parallels, although the verb <foreign xml:lang=\"grc\">παρακείμαι</foreign> is found in funerary inscriptions (IEphesos 2200B, 2313B, 2407, IGBulg 1959). In this case, it may refer to a deceased (whose name must have been in the accusative case) or, as Korhonen also assumes, to the vessel that contained her. According to the scholar, the burial must have been inside a church dedicated to Saint Hilarion (and therefore emends <foreign xml:lang=\"grc\">Ἱλαρῶνος</foreign> into the more common <foreign xml:lang=\"grc\">Ἱλαρίωνος</foreign>), the Egyptian hermit who had spent three years in the Pachino promontory around 363 CE (Hier. Vit. Sancti Hilarionis 34-38).</p>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"bibliography\">\n                <listBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    <bibl>\n                        <author>Amico</author>\n                        <date>1741</date>\n                        <citedRange>274 no.2</citedRange>\n                        <ptr target=\"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F5INCW3T\"/>\n                    <ref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002186\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002186</ref></bibl>\n                    <bibl>\n                        <author>Ferrara</author>\n                        <date>1829</date>\n                        <citedRange>383 no.7</citedRange>\n                        <ptr target=\"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/82T4IWDN\"/>\n                    <ref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002005\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002005</ref></bibl>\n                    <bibl type=\"corpus\" n=\"IMusCatania\">\n                        <citedRange>189</citedRange>\n                        <ptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/2EUC82DH\"/>\n                    <ref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028</ref></bibl>\n                    <bibl/>\n                </listBibl>\n\t   <listBibl type=\"discussion\"><bibl/></listBibl>\n            </div>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>\n",
